{"TopicId":50014,"ForumId":29,"TopicTitle":"Anybody know how to get the locations of the Centre of Mass and Thrust Indicators?","CreatedByName":"tom1499","CreatedById":38308,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T06:08:58Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tom1499","CreatedById":38308,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T06:08:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ETitle says it all. I\u0027m looking to make a plugin that tells you the offset of the CoM and CoT indicators.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEDIT: Solved! See my bottom post.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-10-24T17:38:26Z\u0022 title=\u002210/24/2013 05:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 24, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by tom1499\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tom1499","CreatedById":38308,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-22T07:49:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOkay, I have found it in the object editor, still doesn\u0027t give me a way to get the vectors.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"numerobis","CreatedById":62016,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-23T03:05:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003Evessel.findWorldCenterOfMass();\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eor local, depending on what you want. Doesn\u0027t seem like you can find the CoT quite so easily.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/numerobis/MechJeb2/commit/45d8854a2470592da303e7e4b4d967ca91143d90\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis patch\u003C/a\u003E may perhaps be of use in computing it by hand.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-10-23T03:09:43Z\u0022 title=\u002210/23/2013 03:09  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 23, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by numerobis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tom1499","CreatedById":38308,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-10-24T17:34:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOk I seem to have got it with this:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFirst:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003Epublic static GameObject CoM;\u003Cbr\u003EEditorVesselOverlays vesselOverlays;\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThen:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003EvesselOverlays = (EditorVesselOverlays)GameObject.FindObjectOfType(typeof(EditorVesselOverlays));\u003Cbr\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eand finally:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode\u0022\u003ECoM = vesselOverlays.CoMmarker.gameObject;\u003C/pre\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECase closed.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}